21:15.704 --> 21:25.317
Two men bring an offering to the Lord, one of the fruit of the ground, the other, the first born of His flock.

21:25.337 --> 21:28.020
God accepts one and rejects the other.

21:29.002 --> 21:29.362
Why?

21:31.234 --> 21:35.320
Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.

21:36.221 --> 21:41.788
And in the process of time, it came to pass that Cain brought an offering of the fruit of the ground to the Lord.

21:42.569 --> 21:45.934
Abel also brought the firstborn of his flock and of their fat.

21:46.995 --> 21:52.503
The word tells us clearly that the offering Abel brought was the firstborn of his flock.

21:52.523 --> 21:55.948
But it doesn't say that Cain brought the first fruits of his crops.

21:56.849 --> 22:00.594
It simply says, in the process of time Cain brought an offering.

22:01.154 --> 22:05.039
