22:08.784 --> 22:12.409
God accepted Abel's offering because it was the first of his increase.

22:13.210 --> 22:17.016
Cain's offering was rejected because it wasn't the first of his.

22:18.257 --> 22:20.460
Giving the first to God requires faith.

22:21.161 --> 22:27.350
When a first born lamb is born in a flock, it's not possible to know how many more lambs that you might produce.

22:27.490 --> 22:30.674
But Abel gave his first born lamb in faith.

22:31.106 --> 22:36.393
Whereas Cain made sure he had enough for himself before giving to God.

22:36.413 --> 22:44.182
Many of us treat God the same way as Cain, making sure we have enough money before we see if there's anything left for God.

22:44.803 --> 22:50.330
Even if we give from what's left over, God can't accept the offering because it's not the first fruit.

22:51.151 --> 22:53.394
Other stories emphasize this truth.

22:53.666 --> 23:01.374
In the account of the fall of Jericho, the Lord gave strict instructions that the Israelites were not to keep any of the spoils from Jericho.

23:01.935 --> 23:04.077
All of it belonged to him, the Lord declared.

23:04.678 --> 23:09.223
Jericho belonged to the Lord because it was the first city conquered in the promised land.

23:09.764 --> 23:11.966
It was the first fruits.

23:12.006 --> 23:16.671
God withheld his blessing from Israel when one man took some of the spoils for himself.

23:17.392 --> 23:19.154
The first belongs to God.

23:20.066 --> 23:24.732
There was much more at stake than money when Abraham offered his firstborn son Isaac.

23:25.473 --> 23:30.539
When God asked for his son, Abraham didn't wait to have ten sons before giving Isaac.

23:31.139 --> 23:34.283
He gave the first when he only had one to give.

23:35.264 --> 23:37.747
Abraham had only the promise of having no sons.

23:38.308 --> 23:40.691
It took faith for Abraham to offer Isaac.

23:41.372 --> 23:43.614
Faith that God respected and blessed.

23:44.716 --> 23:46.358
And God did the same for us.

23:47.399 --> 23:50.002
He gave his first in the form of his son.

23:50.338 --> 23:55.164
He's first and only begotten the Son, who has given to us while we were still sinners.

23:56.186 --> 24:00.592
God gave Jesus in faith that we might one day give our lives to Him.

24:01.493 --> 24:06.259
The gift of His Son came before the blessing of our repentance and salvation.

24:07.180 --> 24:09.684
We give our first fruits in much the same way.

24:10.465 --> 24:15.612
Before we see the blessing of God, we give it in faith.

24:15.632 --> 24:20.338
Giving the first fruit of your income says to God, I recognize you first.

24:20.674 --> 24:26.180
I'm putting you first in my life, and I trust you to take care of the rest.

24:37.574 --> 24:48.146
Oh, of first fruits, it challenges us to prioritize God in our finances, even when times are tough.

24:49.442 --> 24:51.304
It's a principle for us to learn.

24:51.364 --> 24:53.726
It's a principle for us to practice.

24:55.888 --> 24:59.912
That no matter what, what was the phrase that came over in faith?

25:00.913 --> 25:05.377
Believing, knowing that God is able, that God is going to take care of.

25:10.082 --> 25:18.290
In a community where financial pressure is a reality, in the city of St. Louis, again, we only need to look at

25:19.362 --> 25:20.484
newspaper headlines.

25:23.531 --> 25:29.464
This principle is a reminder that putting God first in our finances is a step of faith that he'll bless.

25:30.847 --> 25:39.986
And when we talk about offering hope and healing, we have to understand that principle before we can ever help somebody else.

25:40.802 --> 25:50.615
We have to understand how to manage our resources wisely, because stewardship isn't only about giving, but it's about managing what God has entrusted to us.

25:50.936 --> 25:54.981
Proverbs chapter 20, I'm sorry, 21 and verse 20.

25:56.663 --> 25:59.928
Guys, you'll need to put that there for me, thank you.

25:59.948 --> 26:05.595
Says that the wise have wealth and luxury, but fools spend whatever they get.

26:08.859 --> 26:10.802
If you know what a litmus test is,

26:12.034 --> 26:15.598
Simply a test that you can take against yourself.

26:17.521 --> 26:19.223
Where do you fall on these two?

26:19.283 --> 26:20.184
There's two categories.

26:21.165 --> 26:26.151
The whys have wealth and luxury, but fools spend whatever they get.

26:27.192 --> 26:35.382
Now situations may dictate that money gets spent and you kind of have to go down to the end of the money before the end of the month.

26:37.565 --> 26:41.810
But the wisdom is is that as we talked last year in our stewardship campaign,

26:43.138 --> 26:50.709
that we learn how to budget, we learn how to give our money, an assignment, we make our money work for us, we don't work for it.

26:50.809 --> 26:51.811
Do you remember that phrase?

26:53.473 --> 26:57.098
Money works for us, we don't work for money.

27:01.484 --> 27:08.114
See this passage highlights the importance of planning, saving, and wisely managing

27:08.418 --> 27:10.482
the resources that God has entrusted to us.

27:10.843 --> 27:22.546
Practical stewardship in our community can involve budgeting, avoiding unnecessary debt, and making wise investments that can help not only ourselves but others in the long run.

27:24.971 --> 27:28.498
And then finally, the third way that we can be effective witnesses

27:28.578 --> 27:38.585
to the city of St. Louis offering hope and healing is by encouraging community empowerment through entrepreneurship and job creation.

27:38.966 --> 27:41.733
Now, the first two are about us.

27:42.375 --> 27:43.698
They're looking inward.

27:43.810 --> 27:46.014
We have to manage our resources.

27:46.394 --> 27:53.866
We need to know who the ultimate provider is and we need to be able to communicate that to a lost and dying world.

27:53.886 --> 27:56.370
We need to be able to practice what we know.

27:56.651 --> 28:02.480
We know that the father is the ultimate and we need to be able to practice that in our daily lives.

28:02.921 --> 28:03.261
Why?

28:03.282 --> 28:06.066
This third point answers the why.

28:06.370 --> 28:10.477
It's so that we can then take and go outside these four walls.

28:10.797 --> 28:17.368
We can take our message of being hope and healing to the city of St. Louis.

28:18.610 --> 28:23.378
Deuteronomy chapter eight and verse 18 says, remember the Lord, your God.

28:23.779 --> 28:32.914
He is the one who gives you power to be successful in order to fulfill the covenant he confirmed to your ancestors with an oath.

28:33.442 --> 28:36.026
He is the one who provides the power.

28:36.567 --> 28:47.204
We have an opportunity to communicate, to share, to empower individuals with God-given abilities if we can lead them to the foot of the cross.

28:47.805 --> 28:52.472
God has given each one of us unique talents and abilities to create wealth.

28:53.974 --> 29:01.426
In a community like ours where economic disparity is prevalent, listen, you don't need to look anywhere farther than out, well,

29:01.506 --> 29:11.118
I start to see out our front doors, but it's probably more apropos to look out our back door and look at the big huge mansions that literally butt up against the back of our property.

29:11.479 --> 29:20.150
And if you were to drive Hawthorne and I forget the name of the other street, but and loop around those that neighborhood and the beautiful mansions.

29:20.530 --> 29:29.682
And then if you were to drive just a few blocks, the disparity from those houses to those houses,

29:30.978 --> 29:31.799
is night and day.

29:35.823 --> 29:40.327
It's essential for us to encourage our neighbors.

29:42.609 --> 29:48.495
It's upon us to offer hope and healing.

29:49.476 --> 29:53.179
How do we connect with a city that is in such need?

29:53.680 --> 29:56.943
How does the church become the hands and feet of Jesus?

29:56.963 --> 29:58.004
What did Jesus do?

29:59.525 --> 30:00.146
He went

30:00.610 --> 30:04.476
to the struggling fishermen, they weren't having a very good day, were they?

30:07.199 --> 30:09.503
They were throwing their nets and they weren't catching anything.

30:09.523 --> 30:14.350
So what was the economic outcome or outlook, poverty?

30:14.970 --> 30:16.052
They were struggling.

30:17.434 --> 30:22.802
And he comes and he says, hey, listen, I'm paraphrasing, putting a couple stories together, you get the concept.

30:24.063 --> 30:24.584
He's like, listen.

30:25.385 --> 30:27.088
Number one, three nets on the other side.

30:27.468 --> 30:28.690
This isn't rocket science.

30:29.730 --> 30:31.873
But I'm going to bless you, throw your nuts on the other side.

30:34.077 --> 30:35.680
He says, come and follow me.

30:37.242 --> 30:39.045
I'm going to show you a better way.

30:39.145 --> 30:40.848
I'm going to make you fishers of men.

30:40.868 --> 30:44.454
He says, I'm going to take you and I'm going to train you.

30:44.794 --> 30:49.202
I'm going to walk you through and I'm going to give you a different direction to walk in life.

30:49.442 --> 30:51.986
I'm going to take care of your spiritual need.

30:52.162 --> 30:55.666
And in so doing, I'm also then, what would we talk about earlier?

30:55.947 --> 30:58.029
I'm gonna provide for your physical need.

30:58.350 --> 31:01.574
I'm gonna take the two together and I'm gonna provide for you.

31:01.594 --> 31:18.796
And so we as the church, being the hands and feet of Jesus, how can we take a community and say, listen, come, we will train you, we will teach you, we will answer the spiritual need, but we'll also help you with the physical need.

31:19.096 --> 31:20.498
We'll help you meet

31:20.674 --> 31:22.017
physical situations.

31:22.258 --> 31:31.059
We need to recognize and nurture God-given abilities in other people, helping individuals in our community.

31:32.242 --> 31:32.643
I don't know.

31:32.703 --> 31:35.530
I'm just what we would call, say, spitballing this.

31:35.891 --> 31:37.074
But what if

31:37.314 --> 31:39.516
We helped them start businesses.

31:39.556 --> 31:41.938
We have people in our church that are doctors.

31:42.298 --> 31:45.141
We have people in our church that are experts in finance.

31:45.161 --> 31:48.003
We have people in our church that are expert in mental health.

31:48.264 --> 31:51.767
We have people in our church who have run or own businesses.

31:52.007 --> 32:00.694
And they've already navigated the situation with city hall and licenses and permits and health department and all of those things that are necessary.

32:00.934 --> 32:03.617
And we can come and say, hey, listen, I've already done this.

32:03.957 --> 32:06.099
Let me come and let me work with you.

32:06.179 --> 32:07.300
Let me partner with you.

32:07.280 --> 32:13.346
because I see that you have a need and I want to be able to be Jesus to you today.

32:15.508 --> 32:24.216
Because see, the church has a role in economic empowerment.

32:25.638 --> 32:34.546
I know we don't always see it that way, but the church's stretch needs to be beyond the four walls of this building.

32:36.386 --> 32:52.041
If your heart is only the church and you come and you get here inside these four walls, now I don't want you to raise your hand, but how many of you have been to the other parts of our property?

32:53.942 --> 33:02.150
Been to the church office, been down to the basement, the fellowship hall, the space under here, right now it's got a lot of storage stuff.

33:04.212 --> 33:06.354
Been to the second floor, third floor,

33:09.666 --> 33:12.590
I would guess I hope most of you, but maybe not.

33:14.793 --> 33:19.719
But our church exists beyond just this room or these two rooms.

33:21.862 --> 33:29.832
And the reach and the hands of the church need to exist and stretch out beyond even the property boundaries.

33:34.077 --> 33:37.842
The church has a role in supporting, keyword supporting,

33:39.170 --> 33:41.333
job creation and entrepreneurship.

33:43.356 --> 33:55.935
We might offer things like training programs, financial literacy courses, networking opportunities, opportunities to connect individuals with resources and mentors.

33:55.975 --> 34:03.927
Some of us work at companies that if we were to say, hey, listen, boss, would you come to church with me or would you come to my church?

34:04.828 --> 34:08.754
Not on a Sunday morning, but on a Saturday afternoon job fair.

34:09.410 --> 34:14.777
I want to connect you with some people that I know that all they're really looking for is a hand up.

34:15.358 --> 34:17.381
All they're not looking for a handout.

34:17.901 --> 34:19.123
They're looking for a hand up.

34:19.163 --> 34:23.709
They've struggled for six months, nine months, a year to find a job.

34:24.190 --> 34:33.522
They already have a degree in X or they're willing to be trained in our entry level position that our company provides.

34:37.090 --> 34:49.742
We have opportunities to take what God has given us physical things, not just our spiritual, and offer it beyond the four walls.

34:52.565 --> 34:54.567
The early church did this to a degree.

34:54.767 --> 34:56.989
Look at Acts chapter two verses 44 through 45.

34:57.230 --> 35:05.938
It says, and all the believers met together in one place and shared everything they had.

35:06.018 --> 35:10.504
They sold their property and possessions and shared the money with those in need.

35:11.124 --> 35:14.349
They created a community that supported each other.

35:16.712 --> 35:25.783
See, today we can follow this model by creating initiatives that provide economic opportunities within our community, reflecting God's love and provision.

35:28.747 --> 35:34.354
Many of you know, but not all of you know, this last year, this year we created another nonprofit,

35:35.426 --> 35:38.191
that we call Berea community outreach.

35:38.211 --> 35:39.173
Now why did we do that?

35:39.233 --> 35:54.121
Because we have a daycare and under our Assemblies of God non-profit status, we can't have those kinds of ministries because our non-profit status as an organization comes from the National Assemblies of God office through the district office down to us.

35:54.602 --> 35:59.090
There's rules that we have to follow according to them and according to the federal government.

35:59.746 --> 36:04.291
So to be able to provide our daycare and to do what we were doing there, we had to have another.

36:04.351 --> 36:08.736
So this is different than maybe a different nonprofit.

36:08.756 --> 36:12.280
This one is we are Berea Temple International Church.

36:12.320 --> 36:13.722
We're Berea Temple legally.

36:14.763 --> 36:16.545
And then we have Berea Community Outreach.

36:17.987 --> 36:19.929
There are two sides of the same coin.

36:20.369 --> 36:21.631
One side is our church.

36:22.552 --> 36:28.018
The other side is our outreach opportunity to be able to do stuff as the church

36:29.122 --> 36:29.623
together.

36:31.968 --> 36:37.160
Same organization, now they have separate boards because the federal government requires that.

36:39.425 --> 36:40.808
But we have two opportunities.

36:41.309 --> 36:47.282
This is where Berea Community Outreach comes into play in the practical side

36:47.362 --> 36:56.394
of the life of the church is being able to take things like these training classes, being able to offer these initiatives that we just talked about.

36:56.414 --> 37:12.136
And we can have, we now have the ability to put an umbrella in place and say, hey, listen, we as Berea Temple, Berea Temple, the church, the outreach, want to offer hope and healing to our community.

37:14.118 --> 37:16.722
But it all starts with us.

37:16.962 --> 37:18.444
It all starts with ourselves.

37:18.524 --> 37:21.428
It all starts here in our individual hearts.

37:23.171 --> 37:27.777
So as we close, we're gonna kind of wrap this up.

37:27.817 --> 37:38.752
We talked about two things that are inward and we talked about the second one or the reason, if you will, the why of why we need to do this.

37:40.174 --> 37:43.218
I want us to take one last look at the empty jar.

37:44.380 --> 37:46.002
Sitting up here on the communion table,

37:48.034 --> 37:52.039
The jar represents more than just a simple illustration for my sermon.

37:52.359 --> 37:58.046
It symbolizes our journey of faith and our trust in God's provision.

37:59.908 --> 38:07.517
Throughout our time, our message today, we looked at how at our lives, like this jar, and how they may feel empty.

38:08.198 --> 38:14.866
Whether it's due to financial struggles, a lack of direction, or overwhelming pressures that life puts upon us.

38:16.578 --> 38:19.041
But the message that we want to share today is this.

38:20.743 --> 38:33.417
God is ready to fill our empty jars overflowing them with his provision, wisdom, and grace, both individually and as a church, corporately.

38:39.244 --> 38:40.865
So I want us to look back on our message.

38:43.148 --> 38:45.010
We looked at trusting in God's provision,

38:46.434 --> 38:52.083
Just as I shared my pastor's story at the beginning, we're reminded that God is our ultimate provider.

38:52.444 --> 38:59.055
When we place our trust in Him, He meets our needs according to His riches and His glory, not ours.

39:01.819 --> 39:08.370
Whether we see the jar as half empty or half full, God sees it as overflowing with His blessing.

39:11.202 --> 39:14.166
Second thing we looked at was practicing biblical stewardship.

39:14.206 --> 39:19.612
We honor God when we give Him our first fruits, and we manage our resources wisely.

39:20.533 --> 39:30.946
Stewardship isn't just about giving, it's about making every aspect of our financial lives a reflection of God's kingdom and His values.

39:30.966 --> 39:37.234
When we manage well what He's given us, we position ourselves to be a blessing to others.

39:38.658 --> 39:41.261
And then the last thing we looked at was empowering our community.

39:43.544 --> 39:49.431
We're called to take what God has filled our jars with and pour it out into our community.

39:49.791 --> 39:52.474
That is the pouring out of the overflowing.

39:53.215 --> 40:05.810
It's not to just pour out and to cover us, but it is to take the jar and to pour it out into our community by encouraging whether entrepreneurship, job creation, or economic empowerment.

40:06.946 --> 40:16.664
We not only secure our futures, but we also lead by example in our community offering hope and healing to those around us.

40:17.826 --> 40:21.233
Let's pray.

40:21.253 --> 40:28.466
Father, we come before you today with hearts open to the truth of your word.

40:29.474 --> 40:41.973
We thank you for reminding us that you are the ultimate provider, that you care for every detail of our lives and that you have called us to be good stewards of all that you have entrusted to us.

40:43.416 --> 40:52.049
We ask for your wisdom as we navigate our finances and our resources that we might honor you in everything that we do.

40:53.511 --> 40:55.314
Lord, we pray for our community.

40:55.810 --> 40:57.352
We pray for Compton Heights.

40:57.833 --> 41:00.116
We pray for South City St. Louis.

41:00.416 --> 41:12.473
We pray for the metro area of St. Louis and for those that are struggling with economic uncertainty and for those who feel like their jars are empty, fill them with your provision.

41:12.553 --> 41:13.054
We pray.

41:13.574 --> 41:14.896
Fill them with your peace.

41:15.236 --> 41:25.170
Fill them with your hope and help us as a church to be light in this city leading by example and offering tangible hope

41:25.410 --> 41:27.632
and healing to those around us.

41:29.815 --> 41:31.517
Every head bowed and every eye still closed.

41:32.978 --> 41:46.774
If you're here today and you've never experienced the fullness that comes from a relationship with Jesus, I want you to know that he's offering to fill your jar, your life with something far greater than anything this world can provide.

41:47.054 --> 41:51.839
He offers you eternal life, hope and a relationship with the living God.

41:52.260 --> 41:54.322
If you feel that emptiness,

41:54.722 --> 42:02.252
and you want to experience the fullness of life in Christ today, I want to invite you to ask Him into your heart.

42:02.973 --> 42:11.906
All it takes is a simple prayer, asking Jesus to come into your life, to forgive your sins, and to fill you with His Spirit.

42:11.926 --> 42:17.874
But for those of us that are here and we already know Christ, we already have believed in Him.

42:18.210 --> 42:25.279
This is a call to trust Him more deeply, especially in the areas of provision and stewardship.

42:25.959 --> 42:32.728
Maybe your jar feels half-empty or perhaps you've been holding on too tightly to what God has entrusted to you.

42:34.410 --> 42:47.986
Today, I want to challenge you to surrender every part of your life, your finances, your fears, your future to the Almighty, to the one who is the provider.

42:49.026 --> 42:55.514
Trust Him to fill your jar and then pour it out to bless others in our community.

42:57.377 --> 43:03.805
So as our worship team sings out our final song today, I want you to come.

43:03.865 --> 43:08.891
If you need to give your heart and life to Jesus, I invite you to come and find one of us.

43:08.911 --> 43:17.362
If you would like to find a place of prayer, either in your seat or out at the altar, or if you just need prayer for something else,

43:18.274 --> 43:21.359
Please come as we sing our closing song.

43:23.583 --> 43:26.688
Father, we pray for each soul that is here.

43:26.708 --> 43:33.218
May your word and way have control in the name of Jesus.

43:33.920 --> 43:34.981
The altars are open.

43:35.502 --> 43:37.906
You're invited to come as we sing.

